Erika?

02:44:26.000 --> 02:44:28.790
Erika?

02:44:28.790 --> 02:44:30.790
Oh, man, you're not gonna believe this.

02:44:30.790 --> 02:44:32.790
She was there.

02:44:32.790 --> 02:44:33.790
Donna met me, but...

02:44:33.790 --> 02:44:34.790
Wait.

02:44:34.790 --> 02:44:37.790
Before you say anything else,

02:44:37.790 --> 02:44:39.790
is this the girl you've been seeing?

02:44:39.790 --> 02:44:40.790
Yeah.

02:44:40.790 --> 02:44:42.790
Yeah, Donna. Donna Mainland. What's she doing here?

02:44:42.790 --> 02:44:43.790
She's dead, Johnny.

02:44:43.790 --> 02:44:48.450
She died in a car accident.

02:44:48.450 --> 02:44:56.250
She was driving with her boyfriend

02:44:56.250 --> 02:44:58.250
and their car stalled on these railroad tracks

02:44:58.250 --> 02:45:01.250
just out by Waterloo Road.

02:45:01.250 --> 02:45:04.250
They both got out that Donna forgot her ring,

02:45:04.250 --> 02:45:09.250
this school ring that her boyfriend had just given her.

02:45:09.250 --> 02:45:12.250
So she went back to get it.

02:45:12.250 --> 02:45:13.250
And the train came.

02:45:13.250 --> 02:45:16.490
The ring?

02:45:16.490 --> 02:45:21.920
She said I had her ring.

02:45:21.920 --> 02:45:22.920
She was there, Erika.

02:45:22.920 --> 02:45:23.920
I swear it.

02:45:23.920 --> 02:45:25.920
I mean, I talked to her.

02:45:25.920 --> 02:45:28.840
She's a ghost.

02:45:28.840 --> 02:45:34.530
And she said that she wanted me to go with her.

02:45:34.530 --> 02:46:07.730
And it's all because of this.

02:46:07.730 --> 02:46:08.730
Don't run from me, Johnny.

02:46:08.730 --> 02:46:12.330
I want you to come with me.

02:46:12.330 --> 02:46:13.330
Look, take your stupid ring back.

02:46:13.330 --> 02:46:15.330
I don't want it.

02:46:15.330 --> 02:46:17.330
Don't you understand?

02:46:17.330 --> 02:46:19.330
It's you that I want.

02:46:19.330 --> 02:46:22.330
You must know that by now.

02:46:22.330 --> 02:46:24.330
Just, just, just leave me alone.

02:46:24.330 --> 02:46:25.330
It's time, Johnny.

02:46:25.330 --> 02:46:26.330
No!

02:46:26.330 --> 02:46:31.460
Johnny? Johnny?

02:46:31.460 --> 02:46:40.150
Are you okay?

02:46:40.150 --> 02:46:42.150
Did you see her?

02:46:42.150 --> 02:46:43.150
Who?

02:46:43.150 --> 02:46:54.270
Sit down and relax, please.

02:46:54.270 --> 02:46:55.270
Yeah, okay. When a ghost comes after you,

02:46:55.270 --> 02:47:00.250
let's see if you can relax.

02:47:00.250 --> 02:47:03.250
Johnny, are you sure it's the ring

02:47:03.250 --> 02:47:05.250
that's making all this happen?

02:47:05.250 --> 02:47:06.250
What do you mean?

02:47:06.250 --> 02:47:15.440
Hello?

02:47:15.440 --> 02:47:25.250
It's for you.

02:47:25.250 --> 02:47:26.250
Me?

02:47:26.250 --> 02:47:40.690
Look, this is all some kind of joke

02:47:40.690 --> 02:47:42.690
and I'm not buying it anymore, understand?

02:47:42.690 --> 02:47:44.690
This isn't funny, so just leave me alone.

02:47:44.690 --> 02:47:47.610
I'm sorry, Johnny.

02:47:47.610 --> 02:47:50.270
I won't bother you anymore.

02:47:50.270 --> 02:48:02.130
You still think this is all a joke?

02:48:02.130 --> 02:48:15.140
You know, maybe all she wants is a ring back.

02:48:15.140 --> 02:48:16.140
Maybe I should give it to her.

02:48:16.140 --> 02:48:18.140
Well, how are you gonna do that?

02:48:18.140 --> 02:48:19.140
You told her to leave you alone.

02:48:19.140 --> 02:48:21.140
Well, then, then I gotta find her.

02:48:21.140 --> 02:48:24.620
Oh, she's really a ghost.

02:48:24.620 --> 02:48:32.820
I can think of a pretty good place to start.

02:48:32.820 --> 02:49:04.260
Hey, you okay?

02:49:04.260 --> 02:49:05.260
Yeah, yeah, I'm fine.

02:49:05.260 --> 02:49:07.260
Just a little jumpy, that's all.

02:49:07.260 --> 02:49:09.260
You find anything?

02:49:09.260 --> 02:49:11.260
Uh, no, you...

02:49:11.260 --> 02:49:20.430
No, look at this.

02:49:20.430 --> 02:49:24.130
Donna Maitland.

02:49:24.130 --> 02:49:26.130
This is it. This is so grave.

02:49:26.130 --> 02:49:27.130
You sure?

02:49:27.130 --> 02:49:28.130
Well, yeah, look at it.

02:49:28.130 --> 02:49:30.130
How many other Donna Maitlands could there be?

02:49:30.130 --> 02:49:32.130
Well, yeah, I guess,

02:49:32.130 --> 02:49:34.130
but how did you know it would be right here?

02:49:34.130 --> 02:49:35.130
I didn't.

02:49:35.130 --> 02:49:36.130
I just kind of...

02:49:36.130 --> 02:49:37.130
Happened to wander away from me,

02:49:37.130 --> 02:49:39.130
get lost, and trip right over it?

02:49:39.130 --> 02:49:49.000
What are you talking about?

02:49:49.000 --> 02:49:51.000
You knew exactly where she was buried, Johnny.

02:49:51.000 --> 02:49:53.000
Why do you think that is?

02:49:53.000 --> 02:49:55.000
Look, I don't know what you mean.

02:49:55.000 --> 02:49:57.000
Maybe you've been here before.

02:49:57.000 --> 02:49:59.000
Did you ever think about that?

02:49:59.000 --> 02:50:00.000
No way, why would I have been here?

02:50:00.000 --> 02:50:02.000
I'm in a cemetery.

02:50:02.000 --> 02:50:04.000
Why don't you tell me, Johnny?

02:50:04.000 --> 02:50:07.570
You remember what happened.

02:50:07.570 --> 02:50:09.570
The car stalled on the tracks, right?

02:50:09.570 --> 02:50:12.260
No.

02:50:12.260 --> 02:50:14.540
And then Donna got out,

02:50:14.540 --> 02:50:16.540
but she forgot her ring.

02:50:16.540 --> 02:50:20.860
Her school ring, and went running back for it.

02:50:20.860 --> 02:50:40.840
And then what happened, Johnny?

