We don't tolerate comedians in this classroom.

03:35:45.540 --> 03:35:47.540
Now pick up your things.

03:35:50.130 --> 03:35:52.130
We'll be having a quiz tomorrow,

03:35:52.130 --> 03:35:54.130
so I suggest you take notes.

03:35:54.130 --> 03:36:17.130
This is not a good start, Mr. Johnston.

03:36:17.130 --> 03:36:25.820
Maybe I'm jinxed or something.

03:36:25.820 --> 03:36:26.820
Yeah.

03:36:26.820 --> 03:36:28.820
Hey, is she okay?

03:36:28.820 --> 03:36:29.820
You don't look that healthy.

03:36:29.820 --> 03:36:30.820
Yeah, I'm fine.

03:36:30.820 --> 03:36:38.480
Hi, Erin.

03:36:38.480 --> 03:36:40.480
Cool necklace.

03:36:40.480 --> 03:36:41.480
Huh?

03:36:41.480 --> 03:36:42.480
Your necklace.

03:36:42.480 --> 03:36:44.480
I like it.

03:36:44.480 --> 03:36:46.480
Oh, yeah.

03:36:46.480 --> 03:36:48.480
It was my grandfather's.

03:36:48.480 --> 03:36:49.480
He was a pilot.

03:36:49.480 --> 03:36:51.480
It's his wings.

03:36:51.480 --> 03:36:54.480
They're silver.

03:36:54.480 --> 03:36:56.480
I noticed that.

03:36:56.480 --> 03:36:58.480
Well, I'll see you tomorrow.

03:36:58.480 --> 03:36:59.480
Yeah.

03:36:59.480 --> 03:37:02.480
Erin's got a girlfriend.

03:37:02.480 --> 03:37:03.480
Do not.

03:37:03.480 --> 03:37:04.480
Do not?

03:37:04.480 --> 03:37:05.480
Do not.

03:37:05.480 --> 03:37:06.480
I don't.

03:37:06.480 --> 03:37:39.510
Leave me.

03:37:39.510 --> 03:37:48.100
Wow, cool dream.

03:37:48.100 --> 03:37:49.100
You're controlled.

03:37:49.100 --> 03:37:52.100
Trace a door in a wall with chalk so white.

03:37:52.100 --> 03:38:01.230
Connie?

03:38:01.230 --> 03:38:16.670
What are you doing?

03:38:16.670 --> 03:38:18.670
Whoa.

03:38:18.670 --> 03:38:19.670
Cool.

03:38:19.670 --> 03:38:24.300
Arobarious.

03:38:24.300 --> 03:38:25.300
Locorati.

03:38:25.300 --> 03:38:26.300
Creature of darkness.

03:38:26.300 --> 03:38:27.300
Come to me.

03:38:27.300 --> 03:38:34.510
Who are you talking to?

03:38:34.510 --> 03:39:09.370
Whoa.

03:39:09.370 --> 03:39:11.370
I just had this nightmare.

03:39:11.370 --> 03:39:14.370
There was this, this nasty looking guy

03:39:14.370 --> 03:39:16.370
and Connie was there.

03:39:16.370 --> 03:39:17.370
That girl from school?

03:39:17.370 --> 03:39:18.370
Yeah.

03:39:18.370 --> 03:39:20.370
Figures.

03:39:20.370 --> 03:39:23.370
You feeling all right?

03:39:23.370 --> 03:39:24.370
Not really.

03:39:24.370 --> 03:39:25.370
I think I'm sick.

03:39:25.370 --> 03:40:16.500
It's Connie, but it says Laura.

03:40:16.500 --> 03:40:18.500
Then who's that?

03:40:18.500 --> 03:40:32.110
Midnight.

03:40:32.110 --> 03:40:34.110
Until midnight we'll be right back.

03:40:34.110 --> 03:40:36.110
Stick around if you dare.

03:40:39.110 --> 03:40:41.110
We're in the fantasy business.

03:40:41.110 --> 03:40:44.110
You look around and you're in another world.

03:40:44.110 --> 03:40:47.110
It's got to be cleaner than reality.

03:40:47.110 --> 03:40:48.110
Friendlier than reality.

03:40:48.110 --> 03:40:50.110
There should be something for everybody.

03:40:50.110 --> 03:40:53.110
When you're number two, you have to have a few things.

03:40:53.110 --> 03:40:56.110
What we've got is a very exciting ride.

03:40:56.110 --> 03:40:58.110
If you're not a chicken.

03:40:58.110 --> 03:41:01.110
No matter where you live, there's six bikes near you.

03:41:01.110 --> 03:41:07.110
Get your tickets at the gate or in advance by calling 214-706-0606.

03:41:07.110 --> 03:41:09.110
That cute little street in Spain.

03:41:09.110 --> 03:41:12.110
A scene worth preserving on film.

03:41:12.110 --> 03:41:14.110
You raise your camera and say to yourself,

03:41:14.110 --> 03:41:17.110
gee, what's that noise?

03:41:17.110 --> 03:41:19.110
Why risk your camera when you can use ours?

03:41:19.110 --> 03:41:34.660
Fuji quick snap, one-time use cameras.

03:41:34.660 --> 03:41:35.660
Did you see it?

03:41:35.660 --> 03:41:37.660
What? Why are you screaming?

03:41:37.660 --> 03:41:39.660
There was a ghost.

03:41:39.660 --> 03:41:40.660
More ghost stories.

03:41:40.660 --> 03:41:43.660
But this one's for real.

03:41:43.660 --> 03:41:45.660
I think you've got a fever.

03:41:45.660 --> 03:41:47.660
Have you guys been up all night?

03:41:47.660 --> 03:41:49.660
There was a ghost.

03:41:49.660 --> 03:41:50.660
It came through the wall.

03:41:50.660 --> 03:41:51.660
Guys, enough.

03:41:51.660 --> 03:41:53.660
Look, I want you both in bed right now.

03:41:53.660 --> 03:41:54.660
Come on. Let's go.

03:41:54.660 --> 03:41:56.660
Now.

03:41:56.660 --> 03:41:59.940
I'm sure you're okay.

03:41:59.940 --> 03:42:00.940
No, I'm not okay.

03:42:00.940 --> 03:42:01.940
A ghost has tried to get...

03:42:01.940 --> 03:42:03.940
Go to sleep.

03:42:03.940 --> 03:42:05.940
You'll feel better in the morning.

03:42:05.940 --> 03:42:15.020
Good night, guys.

03:42:15.020 --> 03:42:19.300
And no more ghost stories.

03:42:21.300 --> 03:42:41.700
I do this all the time.

03:42:41.700 --> 03:42:42.700
And it just...

03:42:42.700 --> 03:42:43.700
Hi, Connie.

03:42:43.700 --> 03:42:44.700
Hi, Erin.

03:42:44.700 --> 03:42:47.700
Can I talk to you for a minute?

03:42:47.700 --> 03:42:48.700
Alone?

03:42:48.700 --> 03:42:50.700
Sure.

03:42:50.700 --> 03:42:52.700
See ya.

03:42:53.700 --> 03:42:55.700
What's up?

03:42:55.700 --> 03:42:57.700
Are you related to a girl named Laura Turner?

03:42:57.700 --> 03:42:58.700
Why?

03:42:58.700 --> 03:43:00.700
Because I have to talk to her.

03:43:00.700 --> 03:43:02.700
That's not funny.

03:43:02.700 --> 03:43:04.700
I'm not trying to be funny.

03:43:04.700 --> 03:43:05.700
Who is she?

03:43:05.700 --> 03:43:08.980
Laura's my twin sister.

03:43:08.980 --> 03:43:10.980
Who got you to do this?

03:43:10.980 --> 03:43:11.980
Nobody.

03:43:11.980 --> 03:43:14.980
Is there a problem?

03:43:14.980 --> 03:43:15.980
Laura's dead.

03:43:15.980 --> 03:43:24.600
Forget it.

03:43:24.600 --> 03:43:25.600
Wait.

03:43:25.600 --> 03:43:27.600
Have you ever seen this before?

03:43:27.600 --> 03:43:31.330
This is Laura's yearbook.

03:43:31.330 --> 03:43:33.330
Where did you get this?

03:43:33.330 --> 03:43:40.580
Poltergeist.

03:43:40.580 --> 03:43:42.580
Friendly spirits.

03:43:42.580 --> 03:43:44.580
Yeah, right.

03:43:44.580 --> 03:43:46.580
Quicksilver.

03:43:46.580 --> 03:43:48.580
A teenage girl, Poltergeist.

03:43:48.580 --> 03:43:52.580
Known for leaving the letter Q wherever they haunt.

03:43:52.580 --> 03:43:56.460
Q?

03:43:56.460 --> 03:43:58.460
There was a...

03:43:59.460 --> 03:44:09.140
This is Laura's yearbook.

03:44:09.140 --> 03:44:13.860
She had a secret hiding place.

03:44:13.860 --> 03:44:16.860
Behind the wall near the floor?

03:44:16.860 --> 03:44:18.860
Connie.

03:44:18.860 --> 03:44:20.860
I live in your old house.

03:44:20.860 --> 03:44:28.540
I know this is hard to talk about, but how did she die?

03:44:28.540 --> 03:44:37.500
We only lived in that house a few weeks.

03:44:37.500 --> 03:44:43.610
When Laura started telling everyone, she thought it was haunted.

03:44:43.610 --> 03:44:48.890
She found out it was built over an old cemetery or something

03:44:48.890 --> 03:44:52.890
and said there was an evil creature lurking in the walls.

03:44:52.890 --> 03:44:54.890
But she was sick.

03:44:54.890 --> 03:44:57.890
She had this fever. The doctors didn't know it was wrong.

03:44:57.890 --> 03:45:02.740
Laura said it was the ghost.

03:45:02.740 --> 03:45:04.740
Well, what happened?

03:45:04.740 --> 03:45:06.740
No one believed her.

03:45:06.740 --> 03:45:11.890
How could they? They thought it was the fever.

03:45:11.890 --> 03:45:15.890
So she said she had to get rid of the ghost herself.

03:45:15.890 --> 03:45:25.350
She got a book on magic.

03:45:25.350 --> 03:45:30.980
And one night, she lit some candles.

03:45:30.980 --> 03:45:32.980
And no one knows what happened.

03:45:32.980 --> 03:45:35.980
The room caught on fire, and she...

03:45:35.980 --> 03:45:41.600
I think I know what happened.

03:45:41.600 --> 03:46:12.460
I'm not going to get more.

03:46:12.460 --> 03:46:15.460
Weird things have been happening ever since I moved in that house.

03:46:15.460 --> 03:46:17.460
Then I had this dream.

03:46:17.460 --> 03:46:20.460
There was a girl, I thought it was you, but it was Laura.

03:46:20.460 --> 03:46:22.460
I don't want to hear this.

03:46:22.460 --> 03:46:25.460
She was doing some kind of magic to get rid of the ghost,

03:46:25.460 --> 03:46:27.460
but it didn't work.

03:46:27.460 --> 03:46:30.460
She looked at me. She looked right at me, Connie,

03:46:30.460 --> 03:46:33.460
and she said I did it wrong.

03:46:33.460 --> 03:46:35.460
She was telling me how to get rid of the ghost.

03:46:35.460 --> 03:46:37.460
I don't believe it. I can't.

03:46:37.460 --> 03:46:42.190
Look, I'm sorry if this is mean,

03:46:42.190 --> 03:46:45.190
but you didn't believe her the first time.

03:46:45.190 --> 03:46:48.630
And look what happened.

03:46:48.630 --> 03:46:50.630
It's happening again.

03:46:50.630 --> 03:46:52.630
My brother is sick,

03:46:52.630 --> 03:46:57.630
and I'm not going to let any ghost or whatever hurt him.

03:46:57.630 --> 03:47:01.070
I've seen it.

03:47:01.070 --> 03:47:03.070
I believe.

03:47:03.070 --> 03:47:11.500
I need your help.

03:47:11.500 --> 03:47:13.500
Laura's giving you a second chance.

03:47:13.500 --> 03:47:29.870
If that's what you are,

03:47:29.870 --> 03:47:32.870
it does mean you're friendly, right?

03:47:32.870 --> 03:48:07.700
I don't believe this.

03:48:07.700 --> 03:48:09.700
I know. I know. It's okay. Relax.

03:48:09.700 --> 03:48:11.700
What's she doing here?

03:48:11.700 --> 03:48:13.700
She's going to help us get rid of the bad ghost.

03:48:13.700 --> 03:48:18.640
Where's Mom?

03:48:18.640 --> 03:48:20.640
She went to pick up Dad at work.

03:48:20.640 --> 03:48:23.640
Good. We have to do this before they get back.

03:48:23.640 --> 03:48:26.640
I feel so weird being here after all this time.

03:48:26.640 --> 03:48:32.700
This is it.

03:48:32.700 --> 03:48:34.700
This is the stuff Laura used in my dream.

03:48:34.700 --> 03:48:37.700
Mom didn't have the heart to throw them away.

03:48:37.700 --> 03:48:38.700
What are you going to do?

03:48:38.700 --> 03:48:40.700
We're going to fanch what Laura started.

03:48:40.700 --> 03:48:46.350
To trap a creature of night,

03:48:46.350 --> 03:48:49.350
trace a door and a wall with chalk so white.

03:48:49.350 --> 03:48:53.660
Surrounded by candle lights so pure,

03:48:53.660 --> 03:48:56.660
place incense and herbs in a brazier to burn.

03:48:56.660 --> 03:48:59.660
Arabarius, Locaradi,

03:48:59.660 --> 03:49:01.660
creature of darkness, come to me.

03:49:01.660 --> 03:49:15.350
As darkness enters, ready his cage.

03:49:15.350 --> 03:49:17.350
A wand made of oak tied with silver

03:49:17.350 --> 03:49:20.350
will hold the night creature at bay and forbid him to stray.

03:49:20.350 --> 03:49:23.350
Order the night creature into the amulet.

03:49:23.350 --> 03:49:27.350
Arabarius, Locaradi, there he will be for an eternity kept.

03:49:27.350 --> 03:49:59.720
That thing has my brother.

03:49:59.720 --> 03:50:04.180
I don't know if Laura said she did it wrong.

03:50:04.180 --> 03:50:06.180
We must have missed something. We must have.

03:50:06.180 --> 03:50:13.460
It's coming back.

03:50:13.460 --> 03:50:18.640
A wand made of oak tied with silver will...

03:50:18.640 --> 03:50:24.260
This is in silver. It's steel.

03:50:24.260 --> 03:50:32.580
I command you.

03:50:32.580 --> 03:50:38.810
Arabarius, Locaradi.

03:50:38.810 --> 03:50:40.810
I command you. Enter the amulet.

03:50:40.810 --> 03:50:53.650
Are you okay?

03:50:53.650 --> 03:50:57.270
Yeah!

03:50:57.270 --> 03:50:59.270
Guys...

03:50:59.270 --> 03:51:19.550
Look, I'm sorry I didn't believe you, Laura.

03:51:19.550 --> 03:51:57.390
I miss you.

03:51:57.390 --> 03:51:59.390
Because Connie finished what her sister started,

03:51:59.390 --> 03:52:01.390
Doug got better,

03:52:01.390 --> 03:52:03.390
and neither ghost was ever seen again.

03:52:03.390 --> 03:52:05.390
The end.

03:52:05.390 --> 03:52:07.390
So if you're going to use magic,

03:52:07.390 --> 03:52:09.390
make sure you do it right.

03:52:09.390 --> 03:52:16.780
I declare this meeting of the Midnight Society closed.

03:55:44.500 --> 03:55:47.500
You've stumbled onto a delicious story.

03:55:47.500 --> 03:55:49.500
Winner of this year's Emmy Award

03:55:49.500 --> 03:55:51.500
for Outstanding Children's Program.

03:55:51.500 --> 03:55:54.500
Plus this year's Parents' Choice Hall of Fame Classic Award,

03:55:54.500 --> 03:55:57.500
honoring ongoing excellence in a TV series.

03:55:57.500 --> 03:55:59.500
I am speechless.

03:55:59.500 --> 03:56:02.500
Experienced the magic of one of our most popular series,

03:56:02.500 --> 03:56:06.500
Avonlea. Just one of the reasons your family will love the Disney Channel.

03:56:06.500 --> 03:56:50.610
See you later, Dad.

03:56:50.610 --> 03:56:52.610
Thanks for shining my shoes.

03:56:52.610 --> 03:57:01.900
Shoes?

03:57:01.900 --> 03:57:02.900
Thanks.

03:57:02.900 --> 03:57:04.900
They kind of needed it.

03:57:04.900 --> 03:57:05.900
You're all right.

03:57:05.900 --> 03:57:06.900
Have fun.

03:57:06.900 --> 03:57:09.900
Doing something nice is doing something right.

03:57:09.900 --> 03:57:13.900
From the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints.

03:57:13.900 --> 03:57:16.900
Hello! I'm Professor Flurk.

03:57:16.900 --> 03:57:18.900
Today we are conducting an experiment

03:57:18.900 --> 03:57:20.900
to see which is more stimulating.

03:57:20.900 --> 03:57:23.900
Nickelodeon magazine or a herring.

03:57:23.900 --> 03:57:28.500
The subject reading Nickelodeon magazine

03:57:28.500 --> 03:57:31.500
is very amused, very entertained.

03:57:31.500 --> 03:57:35.500
Meanwhile, the subject reading the herring is, well, not.

